<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="913" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d913">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 417.00/57.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-29"><hi rend="italic">July 29,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I transmit herewith, in pursuance of instructions in your June 26,
                            amendatory decree<note n="1" xml:id="d913fn1">As the draft of the
                                amendatory decree given in this telegram is identical with the
                                decree enacted on Oct. 14, the text is here omitted and printed
                                below as the inclosure to Mr. Gunther’s No. 137 of Oct. 31.</note>
                            worded as President Diaz is willing to approve it. The department’s
                            proposed modification of article 4 has been embodied in amendment to
                            article 2, in order to facilitate passage in the assembly.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>